name: Left Ventricular End-Diastolic Diameter (LVEDD)
explanation: The diameter of the left ventricle at the end of diastole, measured in millimeters.

name: Mitral Valve Regurgitation Severity
explanation: The severity of mitral valve regurgitation, which can be classified as mild, moderate, or severe.

name: Tricuspid Valve Regurgitation Presence
explanation: Whether tricuspid valve regurgitation is present or absent.

name: Aortic Valve Area
explanation: The area of the aortic valve opening, measured in square centimeters.

name: Tricuspid Valve Regurgitation Presence
explanation: Whether tricuspid valve regurgitation is present or absent.

name: Left Ventricular Ejection Fraction (LVEF)
explanation: The percentage of blood that is pumped out of the left ventricle with each heartbeat.
